laboratory_examinations.findings: White-cell count: 8400 (normal range: 4500–11,000); Platelet count: 386,000 (normal range: 150,000–350,000); Differential count shows 75% Neutrophils (normal range: 40–70), 17% Lymphocytes (normal range: 22–44), 5% Monocytes (normal range: 4–11), 2% Eosinophils (normal range: 0–8), 1% Basophils (normal range: 0–3); Erythrocyte sedimentation rate: 22 mm/hr (normal range: 0–17).
Aspartate aminotransferase: 133 U/liter (normal range: 10–40); Alanine aminotransferase: 190 U/liter (normal range: 10–55).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Levels rose dramatically to alanine aminotransferase 3566 U/liter and aspartate aminotransferase 2022 U/liter on hospital day 16.

laboratory_examinations.findings: HBV DNA: >380,000,000 IU/mL; HBsAg: positive; Anti-HBs: negative; HBeAg: reactive; Anti-HBe: nonreactive; HBc IgM: reactive.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: By day 30, aminotransferase levels had normalized; By day 65, HBV DNA level declined to less than 60 IU.
